23. Lapse of Policy

17:32.000 --> 17:37.000
A policy lapses if the premium is not paid even within the Grace Period.

17:37.000 --> 17:44.000
Once lapsed, the policy holder loses the insurance coverage and benefits unless revived.

17:44.000 --> 17:51.000
Real-world example, Rohit forgot to pay premiums for 2 years and missed the Grace Periods.

17:51.000 --> 17:58.000
His policy lapsed. He had to revive it later with penalty and interest.

17:58.000 --> 18:01.000
24. Mode of payment

18:01.000 --> 18:04.000
It refers to how often premiums are paid.

18:04.000 --> 18:10.000
LIC allows modes like monthly, quarterly, half yearly and yearly.

18:10.000 --> 18:16.000
Real-world example, Sunita chose monthly payment mode through ECS.

18:16.000 --> 18:25.000
1000 rupees gets auto-dabitted every month, making it easier for her to manage compared to Lumps and yearly payments.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
25. Survival Benefit

18:28.000 --> 18:36.000
Survival Benefit is a periodic payment made to the policy holder during the policy term provided they are alive.

18:36.000 --> 18:39.000
Common in money back plans

18:39.000 --> 18:50.000
Real-world example, in LIC's money back plan, Anuj received 20% of the sum assured at the end of the 5th, 10th and 15th year.

18:50.000 --> 18:54.000
At maturity, he got the rest along with bonuses.

18:54.000 --> 18:59.000
